&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Numaligarh Refinery Limited (NRL).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display:flex;gap:6px;align-items:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Numaligarh Refinery Ltd (NRL) has been granted Navratna status, marking a major milestone for Assam&amp;rsquo;s oil and gas sector.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display:flex;gap:6px;align-items:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NRL has been upgraded to Navratna status.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The announcement was hailed by Assam CM Himanta Biswa Sarma.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Union Petroleum Minister Hardeep Singh Puri praised NRL&amp;rsquo;s performance and growth projects.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Status grants higher financial autonomy and investment flexibility for expansion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display:flex;gap:6px;align-items:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Numaligarh Refinery Limited (NRL)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Located in Assam; a key PSU in the oil &amp;amp; gas sector.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Undergoing major expansion under NREP from 3 to 9 MMTPA.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Promoter: Oil India Ltd; Partner: Engineers India Ltd, Assam Govt.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Navratna Status&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Granted to high-performing PSUs with operational and financial excellence.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Allows greater investment power without government approval.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Sits below Maharatna &amp;amp; above Miniratna category.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Recent Developments&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;2G bamboo-based bioethanol plant commissioned (India&amp;rsquo;s first commercial scale).&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Boosts green energy transition and supports bamboo farmers.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Importance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Strengthens energy security &amp;amp; industrial growth in Northeast India.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Expected to accelerate upcoming refinery and petrochemical projects.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IIT Guwahati &amp;ndash; TIDF.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Indian Railways is introducing the AI-based &amp;lsquo;DRISHTI&amp;rsquo; Locking Monitoring System to detect tampered or unlocked freight wagon doors in real time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;lsquo;DRISHTI&amp;rsquo; is an AI-powered real-time surveillance system for monitoring door-lock conditions in freight wagons.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Developed through a joint initiative between Northeast Frontier Railway and IIT Guwahati &amp;ndash; TIDF.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Enhances freight security by detecting tampering while the train is in motion.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Supports Indian Railways&amp;#39; goal of modernising freight monitoring with advanced technology.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Northeast Frontier Railway (NFR)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;One of Indian Railways&amp;rsquo; 19 zones, headquartered in Maligaon, Guwahati.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Known for innovation in railway safety and technology adoption.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Collaborated with IIT Guwahati on the DRISHTI project.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IIT Guwahati &amp;ndash; TIDF&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Technology Innovation and Development Foundation of IIT Guwahati.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Focuses on AI, surveillance, and industrial automation solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Co-developer of the DRISHTI monitoring system.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI-Based Monitoring in Railways&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Improves real-time surveillance during train movement.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Helps prevent theft, tampering, and operational risks.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Part of India&amp;rsquo;s broader digital and smart-freight modernisation push.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DRISHTI System Features&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Monitors door lock conditions continuously.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Alerts railway operators instantly on detecting anomalies.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Enhances cargo safety and reduces freight losses.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A naval aviation helicopter squadron operating MH-60R helicopters.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display:flex;gap:6px;align-items:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align:middle;font-size:21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Indian Navy commissioned its second MH-60R helicopter squadron designated as INAS 335.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The squadron was commissioned at INS Hansa, Goa.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display:flex;gap:6px;align-items:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align:middle;font-size:21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;INAS 335 is an Indian Naval Air Squadron.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It operates MH-60R multi-role naval helicopters.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The squadron is also known as &amp;ldquo;The Ospreys&amp;rdquo;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It strengthens the Indian Navy&amp;rsquo;s aviation capability on the Western Seaboard.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display:flex;gap:6px;align-items:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align:middle;font-size:21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MH-60R Helicopter&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; &amp;ndash; An advanced, all-weather naval helicopter used for Anti-Submarine Warfare, Anti-Surface Warfare, Search and Rescue, and Medical Evacuation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;INAS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; &amp;ndash; Stands for Indian Naval Air Squadron.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;INS Hansa in Goa is the Indian Navy&amp;rsquo;s premier air station.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The squadron was commissioned in the presence of the Chief of the Naval Staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bahrain.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NPCI International Payments Limited (NIPL) and BENEFIT, Bahrain&amp;rsquo;s leading fintech company, have partnered to enable real-time cross-border remittances between India and Bahrain.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The partnership connects India&amp;rsquo;s Unified Payments Interface (UPI) with Bahrain&amp;rsquo;s Electronic Fund Transfer System (EFTS) via the Fawri+ service.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;T&lt;/strong&gt;he collaboration enables users in both countries to send and receive money instantly and securely.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It was developed under the guidance of the Reserve Bank of India and the Central Bank of Bahrain.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The initiative builds on the 2019 MoU signed during PM Modi&amp;rsquo;s visit to Bahrain and reaffirmed at the 4th India-Bahrain High Joint Commission Meeting (December 2024).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NPCI International Payments Limited (NIPL):&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;International arm of NPCI, responsible for expanding India&amp;rsquo;s digital payment technologies globally.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Promotes systems like UPI and RuPay in foreign markets.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BENEFIT Company (Bahrain):&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Bahrain&amp;rsquo;s national electronic network for financial transactions.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Operates EFTS and services such as Fawri, Fawri+, and Fawateer.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Unified Payments Interface (UPI):&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; A real-time payment system developed by NPCI that enables instant fund transfers between bank accounts using mobile devices.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bilateral Ties:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; India-Bahrain trade (2024&amp;ndash;25) stood at USD 1.64 billion, with two-way investments exceeding USD 2 billion, reflecting strong economic and fintech cooperation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Turkmenistan.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Turkmenistan has legalised cryptocurrency mining and exchanges as part of an economic policy shift.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Turkmenistan legalised crypto mining and exchanges through legislation signed in January 2026.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The law establishes a licensing system regulated by the country&amp;rsquo;s central bank.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Cryptocurrencies are regulated as virtual assets under civil law.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Digital currencies are not recognised as legal tender or a means of payment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Economic Context&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Turkmenistan is a gas-dependent economy with vast natural gas reserves.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;China is the largest importer of Turkmen gas.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The country is exploring diversification through digital economy reforms.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Governance and Reform&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Legislation signed by President Serdar Berdimuhamedov.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Marks a rare economic liberalisation in one of the world&amp;rsquo;s most isolated nations.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Part of broader steps including e-visa introduction and digital governance.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Cryptocurrency Regulation&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Crypto activities permitted under a licensing framework.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Exchanges supervised by the central bank.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Use of crypto as currency or security remains prohibited.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Praveen Vashista; Ministry of Home Affairs.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Former IPS officer Praveen Vashista has been appointed as the new Vigilance Commissioner in the Central Vigilance Commission (CVC).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;Praveen Vashista, a former member of the Indian Police Service (IPS), took his oath of office to join the top anti-corruption body of India.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;He held the crucial administrative role of &lt;strong&gt;Special Secretary (Internal Security)&lt;/strong&gt; in the &lt;strong&gt;Union Home Ministry&lt;/strong&gt; prior to this appointment.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;The oath was administered by the current &lt;strong&gt;Central Vigilance Commissioner, P. K. Srivastava&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;Vashista&amp;#39;s appointment was finalized in &lt;strong&gt;December 2025&lt;/strong&gt;, filling one of the key positions in the three-member commission.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Central Vigilance Commission (CVC)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The CVC is a statutory body governed by the CVC Act, 2003.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It acts as an apex body to investigate and monitor corruption-related cases involving central government employees.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Composition&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The Commission consists of a Central Vigilance Commissioner (Chairperson) and not more than two Vigilance Commissioners (Members).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Ministry of Home Affairs (MHA)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The MHA is responsible for internal security, border management, and center-state relations.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It oversees the Indian Police Service (IPS) and all Central Armed Police Forces (CAPFs).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Special Secretary (Internal Security)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;This office handles vital matters including counter-terrorism, intelligence coordination, and left-wing extremism.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Correct Answer:&lt;/strong&gt; (2) National Maritime Heritage Complex&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;India and the Netherlands signed an MoU on maritime heritage cooperation to support the National Maritime Heritage Complex (NMHC) at Lothal, Gujarat.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The agreement strengthens collaboration for the development of the National Maritime Heritage Complex at Lothal.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;NMHC will partner with Amsterdam&amp;rsquo;s National Maritime Museum for expertise sharing.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Cooperation covers museum design, conservation practices, research, and curated exhibitions.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Lothal reflects India&amp;rsquo;s nearly 4,500-year-old maritime and trading heritage of the Harappan civilisation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Lothal is a prominent Indus Valley site known for one of the world&amp;rsquo;s earliest dockyards.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The NMHC aims to showcase India&amp;rsquo;s long maritime history and global trade connections.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The project aligns with India&amp;rsquo;s efforts to promote cultural diplomacy and heritage tourism.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The Netherlands has historical expertise in maritime trade, navigation, and museum management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To validate integrated multi-domain operations across land, air, and technological domains.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Indian Army conducted Exercise Akhand Prahar in Jaisalmer to validate its multi-domain warfighting capabilities and operational readiness of the newly formed RUDRA Brigade.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operation Akhand Prahar was aimed at validating integrated operations across land, air, and technological domains as part of Tri-Services Exercise Trishul.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It operationally validated the RUDRA Brigade, an all-arms integrated formation capable of infantry, armoured, mechanised, and air defence operations.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The exercise evaluated next-generation battlefield technologies, including drones, counter-drone systems, and indigenous platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It strengthened inter-service coordination, particularly between the Indian Army and Indian Air Force, refining tactics and battlefield procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RUDRA Brigade&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;An integrated all-arms formation designed for multi-domain warfare.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Capable of infantry, mechanised infantry, armoured, and air defence operations.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Name derives from &amp;lsquo;Rudra&amp;rsquo; (Shiva), symbolising strength, and &amp;lsquo;Prachand&amp;rsquo; meaning massive power.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tri-Services Exercise Trishul&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A joint military exercise integrating the Army, Air Force, and Navy.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Focuses on interoperability and modern warfare capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Next-Generation Technologies Used&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Drones and counter-drone systems for surveillance and force protection.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Indigenous battlefield innovations aligned with Atmanirbharta (self-reliance).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JAI Mantra&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;J &amp;ndash; Jointness&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A &amp;ndash; Atmanirbharta&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;I &amp;ndash; Innovation&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Framework guiding modernisation within the Indian Army.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It honours children below 18 for achievements across six categories.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;President Droupadi Murmu presented the Pradhan Mantri Rashtriya Bal Puraskar 2025 to 20 children in New Delhi.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Pradhan Mantri Rashtriya Bal Puraskar is India&amp;rsquo;s highest civilian honour for children below 18 years of age.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In 2025, the awards were conferred on 20 children for exceptional achievements.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The awards are given in six categories: Bravery, Social Service, Environment, Sports, Art and Culture, and Science and Technology.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The scheme aims to recognise and encourage young role models contributing positively to society and the nation.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Pradhan Mantri Rashtriya Bal Puraskar&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is a national-level award instituted by the Government of India for children with outstanding achievements.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The award replaced the earlier National Bravery Awards scheme.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Award Categories&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Bravery recognises exceptional courage shown by children.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Social Service, Environment, Sports, Art and Culture, and Science and Technology reward excellence in diverse fields.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Eligibility&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The award is open to Indian children below the age of 18 years.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Selection is based on measurable impact and national-level significance of achievements.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Objective&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The scheme promotes positive role models among children.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It seeks to inspire youth participation in nation-building activities.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

